name: Maplewood State Park
address:
39721 Park Entrance Road
Pelican Rapids, MN 56572

park_information.Park Information: The maple forest turns brilliant shades of orange, gold, and red in the fall.
park_information.Wildlife: Eight major lakes and many ponds offer water lovers places to swim, fish, boat, and simply relax.
park_information.History: Lake Lida has a sandy beach and large picnic areas for visitors.
park_information.Geology: Drive along the scenic route to observe the wildlife: the park is host to 150 bird species and 50 species of mammals.
park_information.Landscape: The extensive trail system attracts hikers, horseback riders, and cross-country skiers.
